An error page returned by the reporting server reveals the exact version of Microsoft SQL Server Reporting Services which is installed. Information such as this can be used by an attacker during the reconnaissance stage of an attack (for example, knowing the exact version of the software may help them to exploit a particular vulnerability). Therefore, it is considered good practice to exclude information such as this from HTTP responses.&lt;br /&gt;
